What? I can't hold your hand?
- No, of course, you can.

597
00:51:03,240 --> 00:51:06,080
I just think it means
something really different to you.

598
00:51:06,160 --> 00:51:07,280
So...

599
00:51:09,280 --> 00:51:12,800
Okay, tell me something.
You like me, right?

600
00:51:17,560 --> 00:51:20,400
And you think, I'm sort beautiful?

601
00:51:21,160 --> 00:51:25,480
Jake, please...
don't do this.

602
00:51:31,720 --> 00:51:33,240
Why?

603
00:51:36,440 --> 00:51:38,360
Because you are about
to ruin everything.

604
00:51:40,960 --> 00:51:44,360
And I need you.

605
00:51:50,400 --> 00:51:52,320
Well, I've got loads of time.

606
00:51:54,080 --> 00:51:56,000
I'm not goanna give up.

607
00:51:57,120 --> 00:51:59,040
I don't want you to.

608
00:51:59,240 --> 00:52:00,760
But...

609
00:52:01,920 --> 00:52:04,480
It's just because I don't want you
to go anywhere.

610
00:52:08,080 --> 00:52:09,960
It's... it's really selfish.

611
00:52:13,520 --> 00:52:16,760
You know, I'm not like a car
that you can fix up.

612
00:52:20,960 --> 00:52:22,720
I'm never goanna run right.

613
00:52:23,040 --> 00:52:24,960
So I should be fair to you.

614
00:52:27,360 --> 00:52:29,280
It's because of him, right?

615
00:52:39,840 --> 00:52:44,960
Look, I know what he did to you.

616
00:52:46,480 --> 00:52:51,720
But, Bella, I would never,
ever do that.

617
00:52:53,360 --> 00:52:56,880
I won't ever hurt you.
I promise.

618
00:52:58,120 --> 00:53:00,320
I won't let you down.

619
00:53:01,000 --> 00:53:02,920
You can count on me.

620
00:53:10,880 --> 00:53:12,800
Well...

621
00:53:17,280 --> 00:53:19,200
I need to go home.

622
00:53:25,760 --> 00:53:29,560
I'm... I was feeling sick
before the movie, okay?

623
00:53:32,200 --> 00:53:34,400
What is your problem?
- Right now?

624
00:53:34,480 --> 00:53:36,000
You are my problem.

625
00:53:36,320 --> 00:53:39,840
Feeling sick?
Maybe you need to go to the hospital.

626
00:53:40,960 --> 00:53:42,720
Do you want me
to put you in the hospital?

627
00:53:42,880 --> 00:53:46,120
Jake... Jake, the movie's over.
What are you doing?

628
00:53:46,640 --> 00:53:50,160
Jake, you're really hot.

629
00:53:50,840 --> 00:53:53,960
Like, you feel like you have a fever.
Are you okay?

630
00:53:55,040 --> 00:53:56,960
I don't know what's happening.

631
00:53:59,400 --> 00:54:01,040
I got to go.

632
00:54:06,080 --> 00:54:08,000
That dude is weird.

633
00:54:11,360 --> 00:54:12,320
<I>Jake.

634
00:54:12,480 --> 00:54:14,400
<I>Uh, your Dad says you have mono.

635
00:54:14,560 --> 00:54:18,200
<I>He won't let me visit but...
would you call me?

636
00:54:23,360 --> 00:54:26,800
<I>Hey, uh, it's me again.
I just...

637
00:54:27,000 --> 00:54:29,520
<I>I'm sorry about what I said
at the movie theatre.

638
00:54:31,200 --> 00:54:34,720
<I>I just wanted to hear your voice.
So, no pressure.

639
00:54:37,200 --> 00:54:41,920
Jacob, please call me.

640
00:54:42,280 --> 00:54:45,400
Okay, we should be
back around three.

641
00:54:51,760 --> 00:54:53,040
Hey!

642
00:54:53,840 --> 00:54:57,640
Look, I don't have to go fishing today.
- Yes, you do.

643
00:54:57,840 --> 00:55:00,560
Yeah, you do. Go.
What are you talking about?

644
00:55:00,720 --> 00:55:03,720
Just be careful.
- I always am.

645
00:55:05,240 --> 00:55:07,680
Those bears won't get
the drop on me, Bella.

646
00:55:07,840 --> 00:55:10,160
My kung foo is strong.

647
00:55:43,160 --> 00:55:44,800
Jake!

648
00:55:51,560 --> 00:55:53,480
You cut your hair?

649
00:55:56,280 --> 00:55:58,600
And got a tattoo?

650
00:56:01,280 --> 00:56:02,520
Bella...

651
00:56:02,720 --> 00:56:05,240
I thought you were too sick
to come outside.

652
00:56:06,640 --> 00:56:09,760
Or pick up the phone
when I'd call.

653
00:56:10,520 --> 00:56:14,440
Go away.
- What?

654
00:56:16,120 --> 00:56:17,760
Go away.

655
00:56:19,280 --> 00:56:21,600
What happened to you?
What's wrong?

656
00:56:21,680 --> 00:56:24,400
Hey, what happened?

657
00:56:26,880 --> 00:56:29,880
Did Sam get to you?
Is that what's happening?

658
00:56:30,040 --> 00:56:34,080
Sam's trying to help me,
don't blame him.

659
00:56:34,440 --> 00:56:36,360
But if you want somebody to blame,

660
00:56:36,880 --> 00:56:39,760
How about those
filthy bloodsuckers, you love?

661
00:56:39,880 --> 00:56:41,800
The Cullen’s.

662
00:56:48,080 --> 00:56:49,400
I don't know
what are you talking about.

663
00:56:49,480 --> 00:56:51,920
You know exactly
what I'm talking about.

664
00:56:52,200 --> 00:56:55,600
You been lying to everyone.
Charlie...

665
00:56:57,200 --> 00:56:59,120
But you can't lie to me.

666
00:57:00,320 --> 00:57:04,640
Not anymore, Bella.
- Come on! Jacob!

667
00:57:10,400 --> 00:57:12,320
Look, Bella...

668
00:57:13,120 --> 00:57:15,440
We can't be friends anymore.

669
00:57:16,360 --> 00:57:18,560
Jake, I know that
I have been...

670
00:57:19,560 --> 00:57:21,080
...hurting you.

671
00:57:22,000 --> 00:57:25,720
It's... it's killing me.
It kills me.

672
00:57:27,360 --> 00:57:30,640
If you, may be,
give me like some time.

673
00:57:30,800 --> 00:57:32,320
Don't!

674
00:57:33,200 --> 00:57:34,840
It's not you.

675
00:57:37,560 --> 00:57:40,960
It's not you, it's me, right?
Really?

676
00:57:41,360 --> 00:57:44,360
It's true!
It is me.

677
00:57:46,480 --> 00:57:49,600
I'm not good.

678
00:57:51,520 --> 00:57:54,800
I used to be... a great kid.

679
00:57:56,160 --> 00:57:57,760
Not anymore.

680
00:57:58,640 --> 00:58:02,480
It doesn't even matter, alright?
This is over.

681
00:58:02,640 --> 00:58:04,880
You can't break up with me.

682
00:58:06,880 --> 00:58:08,800
I mean...

683
00:58:09,520 --> 00:58:11,440
I mean, you're my best friend.

684
00:58:14,080 --> 00:58:16,000
You promised me.

685
00:58:17,280 --> 00:58:18,800
I know.

686
00:58:19,600 --> 00:58:22,040
I promised that
I won't hurt you, Bella.

687
00:58:23,120 --> 00:58:25,680
And this is me keeping that promise.

688
00:58:26,320 --> 00:58:28,240
Go home.

689
00:58:28,400 --> 00:58:32,720
And don't come back.
Or you're goanna get hurt.

690
00:58:45,680 --> 00:58:47,400
<I>Alice...

691
00:58:47,720 --> 00:58:49,240
<I>Things are...

692
00:58:50,960 --> 00:58:52,840
<I>Things are bad again.

693
00:58:54,160 --> 00:58:58,200
<I>Without Jake, I just...
I can't stand it.

694
00:59:00,560 --> 00:59:02,880
<I>I don't see Edward anymore.

695
00:59:04,480 --> 00:59:07,320
<I>Now it really feels like
he never existed.

696
00:59:14,720 --> 00:59:18,080
<I>I will find a place
where I can see him again.

697
01:00:13,120 --> 01:00:16,480
Bella.
- Laurent!

698
01:00:18,480 --> 01:00:20,760
I didn't expect to find you here.

699
01:00:23,200 --> 01:00:28,080
I went to visit the Cullen’s, but...
the house is empty.

700
01:00:29,680 --> 01:00:32,000
I'm surprised they left you behind.

701
01:00:32,400 --> 01:00:34,320
Weren't you sort of a, um,

702
01:00:35,680 --> 01:00:37,600
...a pet of theirs?

703
01:00:38,080 --> 01:00:39,920
Yeah. You could say that.

704
01:00:40,000 --> 01:00:42,880
Do they Cullen’s visit often?

705
01:00:47,520 --> 01:00:49,040
<I>Lie.

706
01:00:53,920 --> 01:00:56,640
Yeah, absolutely, all the time.
- Lie better.

707
01:00:56,960 --> 01:00:59,520
I'll tell them that you stopped by.

708
01:01:00,400 --> 01:01:03,600
I probably shouldn't tell...

709
01:01:04,720 --> 01:01:06,400
...to Edward.

710
01:01:07,280 --> 01:01:12,000
Because he's pretty protective.
- But he's far away, isn't he?

711
01:01:13,680 --> 01:01:15,440
Why are you here?

712
01:01:15,600 --> 01:01:20,640
I came as a favour to Victoria.

713
01:01:23,200 --> 01:01:24,400
Victoria?

714
01:01:24,480 --> 01:01:26,280
She asked me to see
if you were still...

715
01:01:26,360 --> 01:01:28,560
...under the protection
of the Cullen’s.

716
