01:07:16,600 --> 01:07:18,520
You can do that?

775
01:07:21,320 --> 01:07:23,240
I'll do it for you.

776
01:07:29,560 --> 01:07:33,080
It's not something
I can just run away from, Bella.

777
01:07:33,880 --> 01:07:38,200
But I would run away with you.

778
01:07:41,480 --> 01:07:43,960
If I could.

779
01:07:47,000 --> 01:07:50,600
I got to go.
They'll certainly wonder where I am.

780
01:07:54,520 --> 01:07:56,040
Come here.

781
01:08:00,440 --> 01:08:04,360
Please...
Try to remember.

782
01:08:06,040 --> 01:08:10,920
It would be so much easier
if you knew...

783
01:08:13,480 --> 01:08:16,520
I tried, but...
Jake.

784
01:08:16,760 --> 01:08:19,480
Jake, what are you doing?
Wait, Jake.

785
01:08:26,520 --> 01:08:28,040
Jake!

786
01:08:44,600 --> 01:08:46,360
Edward, I'm scared.

787
01:08:47,000 --> 01:08:48,920
You should be.

788
01:08:53,760 --> 01:08:55,760
<I>Really it's just like an old story...

789
01:08:55,880 --> 01:08:57,640
<I>That we're not supposed to
say anything about...

790
01:08:57,720 --> 01:09:01,320
<I>Did you know, the Quileute are
supposed to be descendants from wolves?

791
01:09:16,200 --> 01:09:17,560
Bella.

792
01:09:17,760 --> 01:09:19,240
I need to see him.

793
01:09:20,360 --> 01:09:22,120
He's not in.

794
01:09:23,640 --> 01:09:25,960
I'm sorry, really need to see him.
- Bella?

795
01:09:42,760 --> 01:09:44,280
What did you do?

796
01:09:45,760 --> 01:09:46,720
Okay, what did you do?
- Hey!

797
01:09:46,760 --> 01:09:47,880
What did you do to him?
- Easy!

798
01:09:47,960 --> 01:09:50,120
He didn't want this!
- But we do.

799
01:09:50,200 --> 01:09:52,280
What did he do? What did he tell you?
- Both of you calm...

800
01:09:52,360 --> 01:09:55,640
Nothing! He told me nothing,
because he's scared of you!

801
01:10:01,280 --> 01:10:03,880
Too late, now.
- Bella, get back.

802
01:10:04,240 --> 01:10:07,480
Paul, calm down now.

803
01:10:15,760 --> 01:10:17,240
Bella!

804
01:10:18,360 --> 01:10:19,880
Run!

805
01:10:22,440 --> 01:10:24,240
Jake, run!

806
01:11:03,000 --> 01:11:04,920
Take Bella back to Emily's place.

807
01:11:06,360 --> 01:11:08,280
Guess the wolf's out of the bag.

808
01:11:13,760 --> 01:11:15,000
<I>Alice...

809
01:11:15,360 --> 01:11:17,920
<I>Is it possible that everything is true?

810
01:11:18,120 --> 01:11:20,040
<I>The fairy tales and
horror stories?

811
01:11:20,600 --> 01:11:24,800
<I>Is it possible that there isn't anything
sane and normal at all?

812
01:11:26,440 --> 01:11:28,240
Hey, I think, we should go back
and see if Jacob's okay.

813
01:11:28,360 --> 01:11:31,080
I hope Paul gets some teeth in him.
Serve him right.

814
01:11:31,200 --> 01:11:34,280
No way. Jake's a natural.
You see him phase on the fly?

815
01:11:34,360 --> 01:11:36,280
I got to fiver says,
Paul doesn't touch him.

816
01:11:36,680 --> 01:11:39,200
Come on in, Bella.
We won't bite.

817
01:11:39,320 --> 01:11:41,240
Speak for yourself.

818
01:11:51,000 --> 01:11:53,760
Oh, hey, about Emily...
Sam's fiancé,

819
01:11:53,960 --> 01:11:56,440
...don't stare.
It bugs him.

820
01:11:58,200 --> 01:11:59,800
Why would I stare?

821
01:11:59,880 --> 01:12:03,720
You guys hungry?
Like I have to ask...

822
01:12:10,600 --> 01:12:12,120
Who's this?

823
01:12:12,240 --> 01:12:14,520
Bella Swan.
Who else?

824
01:12:16,760 --> 01:12:19,560
So, you’re the vampire girl.

825
01:12:22,040 --> 01:12:25,000
So, you're the wolf girl.

826
01:12:27,080 --> 01:12:28,360
Guess so.

827
01:12:28,600 --> 01:12:31,480
Well, I'm engaged to one.

828
01:12:34,360 --> 01:12:36,240
Save some for your brothers.

829
01:12:36,360 --> 01:12:38,120
And the ladies first.

830
01:12:38,440 --> 01:12:41,400
Muffin?
- Sure. Thanks.

831
01:12:41,480 --> 01:12:45,280
Leave it to Jake up to find
a way around Sam's gag order.

832
01:12:45,480 --> 01:12:49,080
He didn't say anything to me.
- That's a wolf thing.

833
01:12:49,200 --> 01:12:51,640
Alpha's orders get obeyed
whether we want to or not.

834
01:12:51,760 --> 01:12:54,040
Alright, check it out!
We can hear each other's thoughts.

835
01:12:54,120 --> 01:12:57,240
Will you just shut up?
These are trade secrets.

836
01:12:57,400 --> 01:13:00,520
Damn it!
This chick runs with vampires.

837
01:13:01,400 --> 01:13:03,560
I can't really run with vampires.

838
01:13:05,880 --> 01:13:07,800
Because they are fast.

839
01:13:08,080 --> 01:13:11,400
Yeah? Oh, we are faster.

840
01:13:12,360 --> 01:13:14,120
Freaked out yet?

841
01:13:15,640 --> 01:13:18,120
You're not the first monsters, I met.

842
01:13:18,280 --> 01:13:21,120
Jake's right.
You are good with the weird.

843
01:13:43,320 --> 01:13:44,840
Sorry.

844
01:13:59,240 --> 01:14:01,160
So you're a werewolf?

845
01:14:02,840 --> 01:14:05,680
Yeah, last time I checked.

846
01:14:07,360 --> 01:14:10,760
A few lucky members of the tribe
that have the gene.

847
01:14:10,920 --> 01:14:15,320
If a bloodsucker moves into town,
and the fever sets in.

848
01:14:17,400 --> 01:14:18,920
Mono?

849
01:14:20,240 --> 01:14:22,160
Yeah, I wish.

850
01:14:24,880 --> 01:14:29,320
You can't find a way to stop?

851
01:14:31,400 --> 01:14:34,400
I mean it's wrong.

852
01:14:36,200 --> 01:14:38,720
It's not a life-style choice, Bella.

853
01:14:39,080 --> 01:14:41,600
I was born this way,
I can't help it.

854
01:14:42,040 --> 01:14:42,880
You are such a hypocrite.

855
01:14:42,960 --> 01:14:45,000
What, I'm not the
right kind of monster for you?

856
01:14:45,040 --> 01:14:49,200
It's not what you are.
It's what you do.

857
01:14:49,360 --> 01:14:51,280
They never hurt anybody.

858
01:14:53,120 --> 01:14:54,640
You killed people, Jake.

859
01:14:54,720 --> 01:14:57,720
Bella, we're not killing anyone.

860
01:14:59,320 --> 01:15:00,720
Then, who is?

861
01:15:00,880 --> 01:15:03,600
We're trying to protect
you people from them.

862
01:15:03,760 --> 01:15:06,480
The only thing we do kill.

863
01:15:08,440 --> 01:15:10,360
Vampires.

864
01:15:11,240 --> 01:15:12,080
Jake, you can't...

865
01:15:12,120 --> 01:15:14,640
Don't worry, we can't touch your
little precious Cullen’s.

866
01:15:14,720 --> 01:15:17,440
Unless they violate the Treaty.

867
01:15:17,720 --> 01:15:19,640
It's not what I'm saying.

868
01:15:20,120 --> 01:15:22,840
You can't kill vampires, though.

869
01:15:23,280 --> 01:15:25,800
They will kill you.
- Really?

870
01:15:25,880 --> 01:15:28,960
We took out that leech with
the dreads easy enough.

871
01:15:33,000 --> 01:15:33,840
Laurent?

872
01:15:34,000 --> 01:15:36,040
And his redhead girlfriend is next.

873
01:15:36,240 --> 01:15:39,200
Vic... Victoria is here?
- Was.

874
01:15:39,280 --> 01:15:41,600
We chased her all the way to the
Canadian border the other night.

875
01:15:41,640 --> 01:15:43,200
But she keeps coming back.

876
01:15:43,280 --> 01:15:46,680
We don't know what she's after.
- I do.

877
01:15:50,120 --> 01:15:51,640
Me.

878
01:16:00,040 --> 01:16:03,200
Don't worry,
we've got this place covered.

879
01:16:03,560 --> 01:16:05,720
She won’t get near you or Charlie.

880
01:16:06,760 --> 01:16:08,360
But you got to be careful.

881
01:16:08,520 --> 01:16:11,640
She's fast, you don't know,
how fast she is.

882
01:16:11,760 --> 01:16:15,200
You know, your lack of confidence
in us is a little insulting.

883
01:16:17,000 --> 01:16:19,240
Alright, I better go.

884
01:16:20,240 --> 01:16:23,920
And you got to go.
- Yeah.

885
01:16:24,520 --> 01:16:26,760
I got a vampire to kill.

886
01:16:40,600 --> 01:16:43,720
<I>Alice, I'm alright.

887
01:16:44,720 --> 01:16:46,600
<I>Until I'm alone.

888
01:16:47,760 --> 01:16:50,280
<I>And lately,
that's all the time.

889
01:16:50,520 --> 01:16:53,240
<I>Jacob's gone,
he's hunting for Victoria.

890
01:16:53,400 --> 01:16:55,560
<I>And Charlie is hunting Jacob.

891
01:16:55,880 --> 01:16:57,240
<I>And you're gone.

892
01:16:58,360 --> 01:17:00,760
<I>And so is Edward.

893
01:17:03,960 --> 01:17:06,200
<I>And I just have nothing now.

894
01:17:09,640 --> 01:17:11,560
You got something, Harry?

895
01:17:12,840 --> 01:17:14,880
Nope, nothing.

896
01:17:22,120 --> 01:17:23,880
<I>But I realize where I have to go,

897
01:17:24,040 --> 01:17:26,240
<I>What I have to do
to see him again.

898
01:20:24,680 --> 01:20:26,440
<I>Don't do this.

899
01:20:30,920 --> 01:20:33,240
You wanted me to be human.

900
01:20:35,600 --> 01:20:37,560
Watch me.

901
01:20:39,840 --> 01:20:43,080
<I>Please? For me?

902
01:20:43,240 --> 01:20:45,560
You won't stay with me
any other way.

903
01:20:48,920 --> 01:20:51,080
<I>Bella. Please.

904
01:22:18,840 --> 01:22:20,360
<I>Breathe!

905
01:22:22,080 --> 01:22:23,600
<I>Breathe!

906
01:22:24,680 --> 01:22:27,000
Come on, Bella.
Breathe.

907
01:22:33,520 --> 01:22:36,640
Bella?
Bella, can you hear me?

908
01:22:42,440 --> 01:22:43,960
Jake.

909
01:22:52,120 --> 01:22:55,120
What the hell were you thinking, huh?

910
01:22:55,560 --> 01:22:57,680
I just needed to see something.

911
01:22:58,440 --> 01:22:59,400
Take her home.

912
01:22:59,520 --> 01:23:01,840
I'm goanna go help over at Harry's place.

913
01:23:05,040 --> 01:23:06,960
What happened at Harry's?

914
01:23:07,320 --> 01:23:09,520
Harry Clearwater had a heart attack.

915
01:23:10,800 --> 01:23:13,320
Charlie and my Dad are at Harry's place
with his family.

916
01:23:13,400 --> 01:23:17,840
Is he okay?
- He's gone.

917
01:23:22,120 --> 01:23:25,120
Come on, I'll give you something to dry
and drive you home.

918
01:23:36,760 --> 01:23:38,960
Hundred and eight degrees over here.

919
01:23:41,240 --> 01:23:42,480
God!

920
01:23:43,600 --> 01:23:45,560
My hands are freezing.

921
01:23:47,440 --> 01:23:49,760
It must be nice, never getting cold.

922
01:23:50,320 --> 01:23:54,240
It’s a wolf thing.
- It's not.

923
01:23:55,000 --> 01:23:58,920
It’s a Jacob thing.
You’re just warm.

924
01:24:01,360 --> 01:24:03,560
You're like, your own sun.

925
01:24:07,200 --> 01:24:11,520
This is better.
Now that you know about me.

926
01:24:14,200 --> 01:24:15,840
But...?

927
01:24:20,600 --> 01:24:23,040
You saw what happened to Emily.

928
01:24:26,440 --> 01:24:27,960
Sam got angry,

929
01:24:28,840 --> 01:24:31,200
...lost it for a split second...

930
01:24:32,240 --> 01:24:34,680
...Em was standing too close.

931
01:24:36,760 --> 01:24:39,200
He will never be able
to take that back.

932
01:24:42,080 --> 01:24:44,000
What if I get mad at you?

933
01:24:55,760 --> 01:24:58,240
Sometimes...

934
01:24:59,760 --> 01:25:02,080
I feel like, I'm goanna disappear.

935
01:25:08,760 --> 01:25:10,680
You need not hear it from me.

936
01:25:15,800 --> 01:25:19,520
But I always will.
You're not goanna lose yourself.

937
01:25:22,200 --> 01:25:24,400
I won't let that happen.

938
01:25:26,720 --> 01:25:27,960
How?

939
01:25:31,280 --> 01:25:33,800
I'll tell you all the time.

940
01:25:37,440 --> 01:25:39,360
How special you are.

941
01:25:58,680 --> 01:26:00,200
Thank you...

942
01:26:00,480 --> 01:26:02,000
...for everything.

943
01:26:08,080 --> 01:26:09,600
Wait!

944
01:26:11,880 --> 01:26:15,280
There's a vampire.
- How do you know?

945
01:26:15,920 --> 01:26:18,440
I can smell it.
I'm getting you out.

946
01:26:19,960 --> 01:26:21,720
That's Carlisle's car!

947
01:26:23,160 --> 01:26:24,400
They’re here.

948
01:26:24,920 --> 01:26:27,240
Bella, it's a trick. Stop!

949
01:26:27,520 --> 01:26:29,040
You got to come with me.

950
01:26:31,920 --> 01:26:33,560
They won't hurt me.

951
01:26:33,640 --> 01:26:36,880
If a Cullen is back here,
this is their territory.

952
01:26:37,600 --> 01:26:40,120
The treaty says we can only
defend our own lands.

953
01:26:40,160 --> 01:26:43,960
I can't protect you here.
- Okay, it's okay. You don't have to.

954
01:26:46,560 --> 01:26:49,960
You’re about to cross a line.
- Then don't draw one.

955
01:26:50,720 --> 01:26:52,360
Please.

956
01:27:08,760 --> 01:27:11,080
Alice!
- You're dead!

957
01:27:11,280 --> 01:27:13,040
Bella?
- What are you...?

958
01:27:13,560 --> 01:27:16,680
I'm sorry, I just...
I can't believe you're here.

959
01:27:16,880 --> 01:27:17,840
Is... Is...?

960
01:27:17,880 --> 01:27:20,720
Would you like to explain to me
how you're alive?

961
01:27:21,760 --> 01:27:24,760
What?
- I saw a vision of you.

962
01:27:24,920 --> 01:27:26,840
You jumped off a cliff.

963
01:27:27,000 --> 01:27:29,200
Why in the hell would you try
and kill yourself?

964
01:27:29,320 --> 01:27:32,720
I mean, what about Charlie? What about...?
- I didn't try to kill myself.

965
01:27:33,320 --> 01:27:34,840
I was cliff jumping.

966
01:27:35,000 --> 01:27:36,360
Recreationally!

967
01:27:36,680 --> 01:27:38,400
It was fun.

968
01:27:40,360 --> 01:27:44,800
I have never met anyone more prone
to life-threatening idiocy.

969
01:27:51,560 --> 01:27:54,800
Did you... did you tell him?
- No.

970
01:27:56,280 --> 01:27:59,520
He only calls once in a few months.

971
01:28:00,760 --> 01:28:03,080
He said he wants to be alone.

972
01:28:08,680 --> 01:28:12,880
Aw, what is that
God awful wet dog smell?

973
01:28:15,400 --> 01:28:17,320
That's probably me.

974
01:28:18,280 --> 01:28:21,120
Or... it's Jacob.

975
01:28:21,680 --> 01:28:23,440
Jacob who?

976
01:28:24,280 --> 01:28:27,000
Jacob's kind of a werewolf.

977
01:28:27,440 --> 01:28:31,600
Ugh! Bella! Werewolf's are not
good company to keep!

978
01:28:32,560 --> 01:28:34,480
Speak for yourself.

979
01:28:39,400 --> 01:28:41,600
I had to see if you were safe.

980
01:28:42,800 --> 01:28:45,320
I thought you couldn't protect me here.

981
01:28:45,920 --> 01:28:47,680
Guess, I don't care.

982
01:28:51,400 --> 01:28:53,600
Well, I'm not goanna hurt her.

983
01:28:55,360 --> 01:28:57,120
No, you're just a harmless Cullen.

984
01:28:57,240 --> 01:28:58,760
We're talking about
the other bloodsucker...

985
01:28:58,840 --> 01:29:00,840
...who tried to kill Bella
because of you.

986
01:29:00,920 --> 01:29:03,920
Victoria?
- Yeah, Victoria has been around.

987
01:29:04,160 --> 01:29:06,080
I didn't see her.

988
01:29:06,600 --> 01:29:09,280
I didn't see you getting pulled out
of the water either.

989
01:29:11,080 --> 01:29:14,080
I can't see past you
and your pack of mutts!

990
01:29:14,160 --> 01:29:17,000
Don't get me upset.
- Hey, stop!

991
01:29:17,080 --> 01:29:19,800
Things are goanna get very ugly!
- Stop! Stop! Stop!

992
01:29:25,760 --> 01:29:28,480
I will give you a minute.

993
01:29:35,720 --> 01:29:39,040
You're going anywhere,
you're goanna come back, right?

994
01:29:39,120 --> 01:29:41,040
As soon as you put the dog out.

995
01:29:50,320 --> 01:29:52,240
Is he...?

996
01:29:55,600 --> 01:29:56,440
Are there others?

997
01:29:56,600 --> 01:29:59,000
How many Cullen’s are here
and how long are they staying?

998
01:29:59,600 --> 01:30:00,840
No.

999
01:30:01,480 --> 01:30:03,400
It's just Alice.

1000
01:30:08,120 --> 01:30:10,440
And she can stay
as long as she like.

1001
01:30:13,240 --> 01:30:15,440
Are the rest coming back?

1002
01:30:21,920 --> 01:30:23,440
No.

1003
01:30:24,920 --> 01:30:26,680
Not that I know of.

1004
01:30:27,400 --> 01:30:29,160
Anything else?

1005
01:30:33,240 --> 01:30:34,880
That's it.

1006
01:30:36,880 --> 01:30:40,000
Well, if that's all, then you better go
run back to Sam.

1007
01:30:43,400 --> 01:30:45,320
I have done it again.

1008
01:30:46,520 --> 01:30:49,040
I keep breaking my promise.

1009
01:30:53,560 --> 01:30:56,280
We don't have to do this to each other.

1010
01:31:00,760 --> 01:31:02,680
Yes, we do.

1011
01:31:14,360 --> 01:31:16,120
Bella...

1012
01:31:19,800 --> 01:31:22,040
Stay with me forever.

1013
01:31:38,480 --> 01:31:40,240
Swan Residence.

1014
01:31:45,960 --> 01:31:47,880
He's not here right now.

1015
01:31:48,800 --> 01:31:50,840
He's arranging a funeral.

1016
01:32:06,440 --> 01:32:07,960
Who is that?

1017
01:32:08,640 --> 01:32:11,360
What?
- Always in the way.

1018
01:32:13,520 --> 01:32:16,360
Who was that?
- Bella, step back.

1019
01:32:16,520 --> 01:32:18,160
Jacob, who was that?
- Stop.

1020
01:32:18,520 --> 01:32:20,040
Bella, it's Edward.

1021
01:32:20,280 --> 01:32:21,520
He thinks you are dead.

1022
01:32:21,640 --> 01:32:24,240
Rosalie told him,
why I came here.

1023
01:32:26,040 --> 01:32:27,000
Why would you...?

1024
01:32:27,080 --> 01:32:28,800
Why didn't you let me speak to him?

1025
01:32:28,880 --> 01:32:30,800
He didn't ask for you.
- I don't care!

1026
01:32:30,920 --> 01:32:33,640
Bella, he's going to the Volturi.

1027
01:32:34,320 --> 01:32:36,240
He wants to die too.

1028
01:32:38,600 --> 01:32:41,240
He left you, Bella.
He didn't want you anymore, remember?

1029
01:32:41,320 --> 01:32:44,560
But I'm not goanna let him
kill himself out of guilt.

1030
01:32:45,520 --> 01:32:47,160
What about your Dad?

1031
01:32:48,000 --> 01:32:48,960
I'm eighteen,

1032
01:32:49,080 --> 01:32:51,280
I'm legally free to go.
And I left a note.

1033
01:32:53,240 --> 01:32:54,760
Please, Bella.

1034
01:32:56,240 --> 01:32:58,840
Just... stay here.

1035
01:33:00,120 --> 01:33:02,040
Not for Charlie.

1036
01:33:04,320 --> 01:33:06,240
For me...

1037
01:33:06,800 --> 01:33:08,720
I got to go.

1038
01:33:14,280 --> 01:33:16,200
I'm begging you.

1039
01:33:18,720 --> 01:33:20,640
Please.

1040
01:33:22,000 --> 01:33:23,920
Bye, Jacob.

1041
01:33:32,080 --> 01:33:33,600
Okay.

1042
01:34:34,640 --> 01:34:36,840
So you made up your mind?

1043
01:34:37,160 --> 01:34:40,160
I'm afraid your particular gifts...

1044
01:34:40,920 --> 01:34:43,640
...are too valuable
to destroy.

1045
01:34:44,000 --> 01:34:47,400
But if you're unhappy
with your lot,

1046
01:34:48,000 --> 01:34:49,760
...join us.

1047
01:34:50,080 --> 01:34:54,120
We would be delighted
to utilize your skills.

1048
01:34:54,640 --> 01:34:57,360
Won't you consider
staying with us?

1049
01:34:59,120 --> 01:35:01,160
You know what will happen anyway.

1050
01:35:01,440 --> 01:35:04,160
Not without cause.

1051
01:35:07,600 --> 01:35:09,520
Such a waste.

1052
01:35:16,160 --> 01:35:17,920
I'm guessing you didn't rent this car?

1053
01:35:18,080 --> 01:35:20,280
I figured, you wouldn't be
opposed to grand theft auto.

1054
01:35:20,360 --> 01:35:21,880
Not today.

1055
01:35:24,800 --> 01:35:28,200
What? What are you seeing?
- They refused him.

1056
01:35:28,640 --> 01:35:31,160
So...?
- He's goanna make a scene.

1057
01:35:31,320 --> 01:35:34,320
Show himself to the humans.
- No! When?

1058
01:35:35,240 --> 01:35:38,080
He's goanna wait until noon,
when the sun's at its highest.

1059
01:35:40,920 --> 01:35:44,040
Alice, you got to hurry up.
- There's Volterra.

1060
01:36:08,920 --> 01:36:11,680
Why are they all in red?
- San Marcos Day festival.

1061
01:36:11,880 --> 01:36:14,720
They're commemorating the expulsion
of the vampires from the city.

1062
01:36:14,880 --> 01:36:16,120
It's the perfect setting.

1063
01:36:16,200 --> 01:36:18,720
The Volturi will never let him
get far enough to reveal himself.

1064
01:36:18,840 --> 01:36:23,160
We have 5 minutes.
- You know, Bella? Breathe.

1065
01:36:29,480 --> 01:36:30,040
Alice?!

1066
01:36:30,120 --> 01:36:32,320
Bella, you're the only one
he can't see coming.

1067
01:36:32,440 --> 01:36:33,560
If I go, he will read my thoughts...

1068
01:36:33,600 --> 01:36:35,520
...he'll think I'm lying
and rush into it.

1069
01:36:36,280 --> 01:36:38,200
Where do I go?
- He'll be under the clock tower.

1070
01:36:38,240 --> 01:36:39,480
Go!

1071
01:38:32,880 --> 01:38:34,520
No!

1072
01:38:36,080 --> 01:38:37,320
Heaven.

1073
01:38:37,520 --> 01:38:39,280
You have to move!

1074
01:38:39,920 --> 01:38:42,920
Open your eyes, look at me.
I'm alive.

1075
01:38:43,360 --> 01:38:45,280
You have to move!

1076
01:38:46,000 --> 01:38:47,520
Bella?

1077
01:38:54,720 --> 01:38:57,440
You're here.
- Yeah.

1078
01:38:59,600 --> 01:39:01,360
You're alive!

1079
01:39:04,400 --> 01:39:05,920
Yes.

1080
01:39:14,880 --> 01:39:17,320
I needed you to see me once.

1081
01:39:18,840 --> 01:39:22,560
You had to know that I was alive.
You didn't have to feel guilty or anything.

1082
01:39:26,080 --> 01:39:29,880
I can let you go now.

1083
01:39:33,400 --> 01:39:35,720
You never had to let it go.

1084
01:39:37,880 --> 01:39:41,120
I just couldn't live in a world
where you don't exist.

1085
01:39:42,880 --> 01:39:45,400
But you said...
- I lied.

1086
01:39:45,840 --> 01:39:49,240
I had to lie
and you believe me so easily.

1087
01:39:54,320 --> 01:39:58,240
Because it doesn't make sense
for you to love me.

1088
01:40:00,560 --> 01:40:04,520
I'm nothing... human.
Nothing.

1089
01:40:05,400 --> 01:40:09,720
Bella, you're everything to me.

1090
01:40:10,960 --> 01:40:12,880
Everything.

1091
01:40:38,360 --> 01:40:40,480
I won't be needing your services
after all, gentlemen.

1092
01:40:40,520 --> 01:40:42,440
Aro wants to speak with you again.

1093
01:40:42,680 --> 01:40:43,800
No rules were broken.

1094
01:40:43,920 --> 01:40:45,960
Nevertheless, we should take this
conversation...

1095
01:40:46,040 --> 01:40:48,040
...to a more appropriate venue.

1096
01:40:48,280 --> 01:40:49,920
Fine.

1097
01:40:50,760 --> 01:40:53,280
Bella, why don't you go enjoy
the rest of the festival?

1098
01:40:53,360 --> 01:40:56,600
The girl comes with us.
- No. You can go to hell.

1099
01:40:58,800 --> 01:41:01,920
Come on, guys.
It's a festival.

1100
01:41:02,000 --> 01:41:04,320
We wouldn't want to make a scene.

1101
01:41:04,800 --> 01:41:06,040
We wouldn’t.

1102
01:41:06,600 --> 01:41:08,240
Enough!

1103
01:41:09,600 --> 01:41:10,840
Jane.

1104
01:41:11,320 --> 01:41:13,840
Aro send me to see
what's taking so long.

1105
01:41:22,560 --> 01:41:24,480
Just do as she says.

1106
01:41:37,000 --> 01:41:38,520
Go ahead.

1107
01:41:42,440 --> 01:41:43,960
Are you scared?

1108
01:41:45,120 --> 01:41:46,360
Are you?

1109
01:41:47,200 --> 01:41:48,440
No.

1110
01:42:20,600 --> 01:42:22,360
Good afternoon.

1111
01:42:26,800 --> 01:42:29,240
Is she human?
- Yes.

1112
01:42:32,160 --> 01:42:35,400
Does she know?
- Yes.

1113
01:42:35,800 --> 01:42:37,440
Then why would...

1114
01:42:39,200 --> 01:42:41,120
She wants to be...

1115
01:42:41,520 --> 01:42:44,520
And so she will be.
- Or dessert!

1116
01:42:53,080 --> 01:42:57,000
Sister, sent you out to get one
and you bring back two.

1117
01:42:57,480 --> 01:42:59,120
And a half.

1118
01:43:00,040 --> 01:43:01,360
Such a clever girl.

1119
01:43:01,520 --> 01:43:04,040
What a happy surprise!

1120
01:43:04,400 --> 01:43:07,640
Bella is alive after all.

1121
01:43:07,960 --> 01:43:11,360
Isn't that wonderful?

1122
01:43:11,760 --> 01:43:14,080
I love a happy ending.

1123
01:43:18,040 --> 01:43:20,240
They are so rare.

1124
01:43:24,040 --> 01:43:26,560
"La Tua Cantante. "
'Your Singer'

1125
01:43:26,720 --> 01:43:29,440
Your blood appeals to you
so much...

1126
01:43:30,320 --> 01:43:32,240
...it makes me thirsty.

1127
01:43:32,680 --> 01:43:35,400
How can you stand
to be so close to her?

1128
01:43:35,560 --> 01:43:38,680
It's not without difficulty.
- Yes, I can see that.

1129
01:43:42,040 --> 01:43:44,360
Aro can read every thought
I ever had.

1130
01:43:44,520 --> 01:43:46,040
With one touch.

1131
01:43:46,680 --> 01:43:48,600
And now you know everything.

1132
01:43:49,560 --> 01:43:51,080
So, get on with it.

1133
01:43:54,280 --> 01:43:58,320
You're quite soul reader yourself, Edward.

1134
01:43:59,160 --> 01:44:00,680
Though...

1135
01:44:01,120 --> 01:44:03,640
...you can't read Bella's thoughts.

1136
01:44:06,960 --> 01:44:08,880
Fascinating!

1137
01:44:12,000 --> 01:44:13,920
I would love to see if...

1138
01:44:14,680 --> 01:44:17,800
...you are an exception
to my gifts, as well.

1139
01:44:20,040 --> 01:44:21,960
Would you do me the honour?

1140
01:44:43,080 --> 01:44:44,720
Interesting.

1141
01:44:46,640 --> 01:44:48,560
I see nothing.

1142
01:44:57,600 --> 01:44:59,520
I wonder if...

1143
01:44:59,960 --> 01:45:03,480
Let's see if she is immune
to all our powers.

1144
01:45:04,320 --> 01:45:06,240
Shall we, Jane?

1145
01:45:07,920 --> 01:45:10,240
No!
- Pain.

1146
01:45:25,720 --> 01:45:27,240
Stop!

1147
01:45:27,840 --> 01:45:29,760
Stop, please!
Stop!

1148
01:45:30,320 --> 01:45:31,560
Stop!

1149
01:45:31,840 --> 01:45:33,760
Just stop hurting him, please!
Please!

1150
01:45:35,000 --> 01:45:36,520
Jane?

1151
01:45:38,520 --> 01:45:40,040
Master?

1152
01:45:43,920 --> 01:45:45,840
Go ahead, my dear.

1153
01:45:51,160 --> 01:45:53,080
This may hurt just a little.

1154
01:46:09,640 --> 01:46:11,560
Remarkable!

1155
01:46:13,200 --> 01:46:16,040
She confounds us all.

1156
01:46:16,440 --> 01:46:20,080
So, what we do with you now?

1157
01:46:20,240 --> 01:46:23,760
You already know
what you're going to do, Aro.

1158
01:46:24,320 --> 01:46:28,640
She knows too much,
she's a liability.

1159
01:46:32,640 --> 01:46:34,160
That's true.

1160
01:46:38,000 --> 01:46:39,760
Felix?

1161
01:47:45,600 --> 01:47:49,120
Please! No, no!
Please!

1162
01:47:51,680 --> 01:47:53,600
Kill me... kill me.

1163
01:47:53,920 --> 01:47:55,440
Not him.

1164
01:48:05,680 --> 01:48:08,880
How extraordinary.

1165
01:48:10,000 --> 01:48:12,720
You would give up your life...

1166
01:48:13,200 --> 01:48:15,120
...for someone like us.

1167
01:48:15,520 --> 01:48:17,200
A vampire.

1168
01:48:18,320 --> 01:48:20,800
A soulless monster.

1169
01:48:20,880 --> 01:48:22,800
Just get away from him!

1170
01:48:26,880 --> 01:48:29,440
You don't know a thing...

1171
01:48:30,560 --> 01:48:32,440
...about his soul.

1172
01:48:33,000 --> 01:48:40,160
Maybe it's one or the other.

1173
01:48:42,760 --> 01:48:45,040
This is a sadness.

1174
01:48:46,800 --> 01:48:51,040
If only it be your intention
to give her immortality.

1175
01:48:59,280 --> 01:49:00,800
Wait!

1176
01:49:02,160 --> 01:49:04,080
Bella will be one of us.

1177
01:49:05,920 --> 01:49:07,440
I've seen it.

1178
01:49:09,280 --> 01:49:11,200
I'll change her myself.

1179
01:49:44,960 --> 01:49:46,640
Mesmerizing!

1180
01:49:46,800 --> 01:49:49,120
To see, what you have seen.

1181
01:49:50,000 --> 01:49:52,320
Before it is happened.

1182
01:49:54,560 --> 01:49:56,160
Your gifts...

1183
01:49:56,520 --> 01:49:59,600
...will make for an intriguing...

1184
01:50:00,080 --> 01:50:02,000
...immortal.

1185
01:50:02,400 --> 01:50:05,440
Isabella.

1186
01:50:08,960 --> 01:50:10,560
Go now.

1187
01:50:11,040 --> 01:50:13,040
Make your preparations.

1188
01:50:13,680 --> 01:50:16,400
Let's be done with this.

1189
01:50:17,680 --> 01:50:20,480
Heidi will arrive, any moment.

1190
01:50:21,760 --> 01:50:23,680
Thank you...

1191
01:50:23,920 --> 01:50:26,800
...for the visit.
- We'll return the favour.

1192
01:50:26,880 --> 01:50:28,080
I would advise...

1193
01:50:28,320 --> 01:50:32,240
...that you follow through on your promise soon.
We do not offer second chances.

1194
01:50:33,960 --> 01:50:35,200
Goodbye...

1195
01:50:35,400 --> 01:50:37,360
...my young friends.

1196
01:50:43,440 --> 01:50:45,040
<I>Nice fishing, Heidi.

1197
01:50:45,360 --> 01:50:47,440
<I>Yes, they do look rather juicy.

1198
01:50:47,600 --> 01:50:49,520
<I>Save some for me.

1199
01:50:50,320 --> 01:50:53,760
<I>This way, please.
Stay together.

1200
01:51:20,160 --> 01:51:21,680
You're here.

1201
01:51:23,760 --> 01:51:25,400
You can sleep.

1202
01:51:28,960 --> 01:51:31,480
I'll still be here
when you wake up.

1203
01:51:35,280 --> 01:51:39,200
Bella, the only reason
that I left...

1204
01:51:40,160 --> 01:51:42,880
...was because I thought
I was protecting you.

1205
01:51:44,880 --> 01:51:47,680
I needed you to have a chance...

1206
01:51:47,760 --> 01:51:51,400
...at a normal, happy life.

1207
01:51:54,800 --> 01:51:57,320
It was so easy for you to leave.

1208
01:51:59,640 --> 01:52:03,680
Leaving you was the hardest thing
I've done in a 100 years.

1209
01:52:10,240 --> 01:52:12,160
I swear...

1210
01:52:12,960 --> 01:52:16,480
I will never fail you again.

1211
01:52:17,920 --> 01:52:19,840
I'm so sorry.

1212
01:52:21,840 --> 01:52:23,760
Charlie's coming.
- Hey!

1213
01:52:26,920 --> 01:52:28,560
You okay?

1214
01:52:29,880 --> 01:52:31,400
Fine.

1215
01:52:34,080 --> 01:52:36,280
Dad, you don't have to worry.

1216
01:52:36,880 --> 01:52:38,840
Yeah, last time you said that
you took off.

1217
01:52:38,920 --> 01:52:41,120
I didn't see you for three days.

1218
01:52:42,840 --> 01:52:45,160
I'm really sorry, Dad.

1219
01:52:46,440 --> 01:52:50,760
Bella, do not ever do that
to me again.

1220
01:52:52,960 --> 01:52:54,480
Ever.

1221
01:52:56,840 --> 01:52:58,600
And you're grounded...

1222
01:52:58,880 --> 01:53:01,400
...for the rest of your life.

1223
01:53:02,080 --> 01:53:03,600
Okay.

1224
01:53:13,720 --> 01:53:16,440
I'm not technically breaking
any of his rules.

1225
01:53:19,320 --> 01:53:22,440
He did say, I couldn't take a step
inside through the door.

1226
01:53:23,080 --> 01:53:25,000
I came in through the window.

1227
01:53:29,160 --> 01:53:31,480
He's not going to forgive me easily.

1228
01:53:34,000 --> 01:53:35,520
I know.

1229
01:53:37,360 --> 01:53:38,960
Can you?

1230
01:53:42,480 --> 01:53:44,480
I hope you can because...

1231
01:53:44,800 --> 01:53:48,080
I honestly don't know
how to live without you.

1232
01:53:52,400 --> 01:53:53,920
Come here.

1233
01:54:11,360 --> 01:54:15,520
Once Alice changes me,

1234
01:54:17,400 --> 01:54:19,440
...you can't get rid of me.

1235
01:54:20,640 --> 01:54:22,880
She won't need to change you.

1236
01:54:23,760 --> 01:54:26,640
There are always ways to keep
the Volturi in the dark.

1237
01:54:28,960 --> 01:54:30,360
No.

1238
01:54:30,800 --> 01:54:32,080
No!

1239
01:54:37,960 --> 01:54:40,280
You all know what I want.

1240
01:54:42,240 --> 01:54:46,160
And I know,
how much I'm asking for.

1241
01:54:47,560 --> 01:54:49,080
The only thing I can think of...
for...

1242
01:54:49,120 --> 01:54:50,920
...it to be fair is to just vote.

1243
01:54:51,120 --> 01:54:54,360
You don't know what you just...
- Just... shut up!

1244
01:54:55,880 --> 01:54:57,240
Alice?

1245
01:54:57,560 --> 01:55:00,000
I already consider you my sister.

1246
01:55:04,040 --> 01:55:05,720
Yes!
- Thank you.

1247
01:55:05,800 --> 01:55:07,280
I vote, yes.

1248
01:55:08,520 --> 01:55:11,920
It would be nice to not want to
kill you all the time.

1249
01:55:15,160 --> 01:55:16,800
I'm sorry.

1250
01:55:18,320 --> 01:55:21,840
I'm really sorry, both of you,
for the way I've acted.

1251
01:55:22,040 --> 01:55:23,280
And I'm really grateful...

1252
01:55:23,360 --> 01:55:26,080
...that you were brave enough
to go and save my brother.

1253
01:55:27,920 --> 01:55:31,440
But this isn't a life
I would have chosen for myself.

1254
01:55:33,800 --> 01:55:37,040
And I wish that there had been
someone to vote no for me.

1255
01:55:40,400 --> 01:55:42,320
So... no.

1256
01:55:43,240 --> 01:55:45,160
I vote hell yeah!

1257
01:55:47,080 --> 01:55:49,440
We can pick a fight with
these Vulture’s some other way.

1258
01:55:49,520 --> 01:55:52,040
I already consider you,
a part of the family.

1259
01:55:53,160 --> 01:55:54,680
Yes!

1260
01:56:00,160 --> 01:56:02,200
Why are you doing this to me?

1261
01:56:04,160 --> 01:56:07,400
You know what this means.
- You've chosen not to live without her,

1262
01:56:07,520 --> 01:56:09,440
...which leaves me no choice.

1263
01:56:10,080 --> 01:56:12,000
I won't lose my son.

1264
01:56:18,240 --> 01:56:20,680
<I>I'll wait until after graduation...

1265
01:56:20,760 --> 01:56:23,080
<I>...to make it easier on Charlie.

1266
01:56:27,320 --> 01:56:30,000
I want you to be the one
to do it.

1267
01:56:37,120 --> 01:56:39,040
He wants to talk to me.

1268
01:56:42,120 --> 01:56:43,640
See, you're still alive for now.

1269
01:56:43,840 --> 01:56:46,040
He thinks, it's me keeping you away.

1270
01:56:46,400 --> 01:56:48,600
You stay the hell out of my head.

1271
01:56:50,080 --> 01:56:51,320
Jacob...

1272
01:56:52,200 --> 01:56:54,240
...I know you have
something to say to me.

1273
01:56:55,960 --> 01:56:58,680
But I want to say something to you first.
If that's alright?

1274
01:57:00,880 --> 01:57:02,400
Thank you.

1275
01:57:05,440 --> 01:57:07,960
Thank you for keeping
Bella alive when...

1276
01:57:08,200 --> 01:57:09,120
...I didn’t.

1277
01:57:09,360 --> 01:57:12,080
No, you didn't.

1278
01:57:13,360 --> 01:57:15,880
And it wasn't for your benefit,
trust me.

1279
01:57:16,080 --> 01:57:17,840
I'm still grateful.

1280
01:57:18,680 --> 01:57:19,640
But I'm here now.

1281
01:57:19,800 --> 01:57:22,520
And I'm not goanna leave her side
till she orders me away.

1282
01:57:22,680 --> 01:57:24,200
We'll see.

1283
01:57:26,880 --> 01:57:29,720
Hey, my turn to talk.

1284
01:57:33,640 --> 01:57:36,360
I'm here to remind you about
a key point in the Treaty.

1285
01:57:37,320 --> 01:57:38,960
I haven't forgotten.

1286
01:57:39,360 --> 01:57:40,600
What key point?

1287
01:57:40,920 --> 01:57:46,040
If any of them bites a human,
the truce is over.

1288
01:57:47,200 --> 01:57:49,120
But if I choose it,
it has nothing to do with you.

1289
01:57:49,200 --> 01:57:51,920
No... No, I won't let you.

1290
01:57:52,720 --> 01:57:55,040
You're not goanna be
one of them, Bella.

1291
01:57:55,200 --> 01:57:57,120
It's not up to you.

1292
01:57:57,840 --> 01:57:59,360
You know what we'll do to you.

1293
01:57:59,440 --> 01:58:01,880
I won't have choice.
- Bella, please come.

1294
01:58:01,960 --> 01:58:03,480
Wait.

1295
01:58:05,280 --> 01:58:07,320
Is he goanna hurt me?
Read his mind.

1296
01:58:15,240 --> 01:58:17,040
Jake...

1297
01:58:23,200 --> 01:58:25,200
I love you.

1298
01:58:29,400 --> 01:58:31,440
So, please...

1299
01:58:35,600 --> 01:58:37,640
Don’t make me choose.

1300
01:58:43,320 --> 01:58:45,240
Because it'll be him.

1301
01:58:48,600 --> 01:58:50,800
It's always been him.

1302
01:58:58,040 --> 01:58:59,960
Bella...

1303
01:59:07,120 --> 01:59:09,960
Goodbye, Jacob.
- No, you don't speak for her!

1304
01:59:15,000 --> 01:59:16,520
Bella, get out of here.

1305
01:59:18,800 --> 01:59:20,040
Stop!

1306
01:59:22,080 --> 01:59:23,480
Stop!

1307
01:59:23,760 --> 01:59:26,480
You can't hurt each other
without hurting me.

1308
01:59:45,920 --> 01:59:47,440
Jake?

1309
02:00:01,920 --> 02:00:03,560
He's right.

1310
02:00:04,360 --> 02:00:06,320
You shouldn't become one of us.

1311
02:00:11,600 --> 02:00:13,520
I can't do this alone.

1312
02:00:16,560 --> 02:00:18,480
Then please just wait.

1313
02:00:25,440 --> 02:00:28,840
Just give me... five years.

1314
02:00:33,640 --> 02:00:35,560
It's too long.

1315
02:00:39,920 --> 02:00:41,840
Then, three?

1316
02:00:45,960 --> 02:00:47,880
You're so stubborn.

1317
02:00:49,640 --> 02:00:51,560
What are you waiting for?

1318
02:01:00,480 --> 02:01:04,400
I have one condition...

1319
02:01:05,920 --> 02:01:08,640
...if you want me
to do it myself.

1320
02:01:12,400 --> 02:01:14,320
What's the condition?

1321
02:01:14,840 --> 02:01:16,760
And then, forever.

1322
02:01:18,640 --> 02:01:20,560
That's what I'm asking.

1323
02:01:31,560 --> 02:01:34,080
Marry me, Bella.

